As the covid 19 numbers continue to climb, more and more places of work are being impacted. And now the receiver of revenue, SARS has decided to close its tax offices for a short period to minimise contact while we ride out the storm. But they say it will still be business as usual online. eNCA's Sally Burdett speaks to SARS commissioner Johnstone Makhubu. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The South African Revenue Service is temporarily closing all its branches for physical visits from next month. This as COVID-19 cases continue to spike but it says it will still be business as usual for services online. READ: SARS eyes offshore wealth Acting SARS commissioner, Johnstone Makhubu says this will help avoid the peak witnessed during the first and last weeks of the filing season.